  "datasetDate": "2026-06-27",
  "datasetDescription": "How to use this showcase dataset: read this description, close it, then select one graph type set (see left panel) and for each graph in that group, click the contextual graph option button on the top right (3 vertical dots) and show/hide the notes associated to that graph. Enjoy!\n\nPalmer Penguins - size measurements for 344 penguins of three species (Adelie, Chinstrap, Gentoo) across three islands of the Palmer Archipelago, Antarctica. Each row is one penguin: species, island and sex, plus four body measurements (bill length, bill depth, flipper length, body mass) and the study year. A few rows have missing values (NA) on purpose - they show how the dashboard handles incomplete data.\n\nA classic teaching dataset for visualization. It demonstrates:\n- Clean species separation across the four measurements: scatter (with marginals), scatter matrix, parallel coordinates and 3D scatter, colored by species.\n- Sexual dimorphism: split violin of body mass by species and sex (males heavier, most pronounced in Gentoo).\n- Categorical structure: parallel categories and sunburst link species, island and sex (Adelie on all three islands; Gentoo only on Biscoe; Chinstrap only on Dream).\nTip: filter by species/island/year in the sidebar, or brush-select on a chart to filter every view at once.\n\nData & attribution\nCollected 2007-2009 by Dr. Kristen Gorman with the Palmer Station Long Term Ecological Research (LTER) Program, part of the US LTER Network. Released under a CC-0 license in accordance with the Palmer Station LTER Data Policy. We gratefully acknowledge Palmer Station LTER and the US LTER Network.\nPackage: Horst AM, Hill AP, Gorman KB (2020). palmerpenguins: Palmer Archipelago (Antarctica) penguin data. R package version 0.1.0. doi:10.5281/zenodo.3960218\nOriginal study: Gorman KB, Williams TD, Fraser WR (2014). Ecological sexual dimorphism and environmental variability within a community of Antarctic penguins (genus Pygoscelis). PLoS ONE 9(3): e90081. doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0090081",
  "descOpen": false,
